cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with regularized training of deep neural networks for classification tasks on image datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the importance of sparsity and weight grouping, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
